# PRISM Document Standard

> Standards for all documents managed by PRISM in {{ project_name | default("this project") }}.

## Document Pairs

Every significant directory maintains two context files:
- **CLAUDE.md** — "What IS here?" (static description, structure, conventions)
- **CONTEXT.md** — "What's HAPPENING here?" (dynamic state, activity)

## Layer-Aware Frontmatter

| Layer | Frontmatter | Metadata Storage |
|-------|-------------|------------------|
| L0 (Foundation) | `<!-- prism:managed -->` marker only | prism.db |
| L1 (Persistent) | `<!-- prism:managed -->` marker only | prism.db |
| L2 (Session) | `<!-- prism:managed -->` marker only | prism.db |
| L3a (Active) | Full YAML frontmatter | prism.db + file |
| L3b (Extended) | Full YAML frontmatter | prism.db + file |
| L4 (Ephemeral) | Full YAML frontmatter | prism.db + file |
| Meta | Full YAML frontmatter | prism.db + file |
| Distributed | `<!-- prism:managed -->` marker only | prism.db |

## Required Frontmatter Fields (L3b+)

```yaml
---
title: "Document Title"
layer: L3b          # L3a, L3b, L4, Meta
classification: reference  # core, architecture, api, guide, reference, template, other
scope: "project/module"
tags: [tag1, tag2]
dependencies: [doc-id-1, doc-id-2]
---
```

## ICM Numbering

Ordered items use `XX-name` prefix convention:
- Stages: `01-spec/`, `02-implement/`, `03-deploy/`
- Refs: `01-architecture.md`, `02-schema.md`
- Contiguous numbering, no gaps
- Gaps are auto-fixed during `/prism:start`

## PRISM Authority

PRISM has **full CRUD authority** over ALL managed documents:
- Creates initial document pairs during `/prism:start`
- Updates documents when drift is detected
- Regenerates derived content on pre-commit
- Classification (derived/authored) is informational only, not a behavior gate
